Summary:
The most important aspect of this project was the transformation of raw, unstructured data into meaningful and high-quality features. Initially, the dataset contained missing values, inconsistent formats, and a mix of categorical and numerical variables, which limited its usability. The most impactful step was thorouhg data cleaning combined with systematic feature engineering. Handling missing values appropriately, encoding categorical variables, and scaling numerical features significantly improved the overall data quality. Among these, encoding and feature creation proved especially critical, as they enabled the model to better interpret patterns that were not directly visible in the raw data.
The primary factor that changed the performance ceiling of the model was feature engineering rather than the choice of algorithm. Creating new features from existing ones and removing irrelevant or redundant features allowed the model to capture deeper relationships within the data. Feature scaling also contributed by ensuring that all variables were treated uniformly, preventing bias toward features with larger magnitudes. These steps collectively improved the model’s ability to generalize, thereby increasing accuracy and stability. This demonstrates that improving input data quality can often yield greater gains than simply tuning or changing models.
From a business perspective, the most actionable features are those that are interpretable and directly linked to decision-making. Engineered features that summarize behavior, highlight trends, or combine multiple variables into meaningful indicators are particularly valuable. For example, aggregated or derived features can help identify key drivers of outcomes, enabling stakeholders to focus on the most influential factors. Additionally, categorical encodings that segment users or entities into distinct groups can support targeted strategies. Such features not only improve model performance but also provide clear insights that can guide business actions, making them highly practical for real-world implementation.
In conclusion, this project highlights that the true value of data science lies in effective feature engineering. Clean, well-structured, and thoughtfully engineered features not only enhance model performance but also generate actionable insights that drive better decision-making.


